<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE topic PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Topic//EN" "topic.dtd">
<topic id="preferences-editor-print">
  <title>Print Preferences</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Preferences<indexterm>Print</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Print preferences</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> lets you configure how files are printed out of the editor. Note that
      these settings cover how files are printed directly from <ph keyref="product"/> itself, not
      how they are printed after the XML source has been transformed by a publishing stylesheet. To
      configure the <uicontrol>Print</uicontrol> options, <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Print</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>.</p>
    <p product="author editor">This page allows you to customize the headers and footers added to a
      printed page when you print from the <xref href="text-mode-editor.dita#text-mode-editor"
          ><uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode</xref> or <xref href="author-editor.dita#author-editor"
          ><uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode</xref> editors. These settings do not apply to the
        <xref href="grid-mode-editor.dita#grid-mode-editor"><uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol></xref>
      <ph product="editor">and <xref
          href="xml-schema-diagram-introduction.dita#xml-schema-diagram-introduction">schema
            <uicontrol>Design</uicontrol></xref>
      </ph>mode.</p>
    <p product="developer">This page allows you to customize the headers and footers added to a
      printed page when you print from the <xref href="text-mode-editor.dita#text-mode-editor"
          ><uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode</xref> editor. These settings do not apply to the <xref
        href="grid-mode-editor.dita#grid-mode-editor"><uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol></xref> and <xref
        href="xml-schema-diagram-introduction.dita#xml-schema-diagram-introduction">schema
          <uicontrol>Design</uicontrol></xref> mode.</p>
    <p>You can specify what is printed on the <uicontrol>Left</uicontrol>,
        <uicontrol>Middle</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol>Right</uicontrol> of the header and footer
      using plain text of any of the following variables: </p>
    <ul>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-editor-variables/edVar-currentFileURL"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-editor-variables/edVar-cfne"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-editor-variables/edVar_cp"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-editor-variables/edVar_tp"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-editor-variables/edvar-env"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-editor-variables/edVar-system"/>
      <li conkeyref="reusables-editor-variables/edVar-date"/>
    </ul>
    <p>For example, to show the current page number and the total number of pages in the top right
      corner of the page, write the following pattern in the <uicontrol>Right</uicontrol> text area
      of the <uicontrol>Header</uicontrol> section: <codeph>${cp} of ${tp}</codeph>. </p>
    <p>You can also set the <uicontrol>Color</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Font</uicontrol> used in the
      header and footer. Default font is <codeph>SansSerif</codeph>.</p>
    <p>You can place a line below the header or above the footer by selecting
        <uicontrol>Underline/Overline</uicontrol>.</p>
  </body>
</topic>
